<h2 class="bac">Our Business:</h2>
<p class="bac">
At Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America Merrill Lynch, Research Analysts are aligned by both product (debt or equity) and industry group (healthcare, technology, energy, etc.). Working alongside some of the most talented professionals in the industry, Research Analysts gain the sector-specific expertise critical to building a career in research, and contribute significantly to the in-depth research we distribute to clients worldwide.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview:</h2>  
<br>
<H3 class="bac">Placement</H3>
<p class="bac">
Associates are hired and placed directly with a specific team.  Placement is determined during the hiring process matching the business needs and the interests/skills of the Associate.   The groups span across country and industry, these include but not limited to (not all groups exist in all countries):
</p>
<ul class="bac" style="margin-top: 6px;">
	<li>Country
		<ul class="bac" style="margin-top: 3px;">
			<li>Hong Kong</li>
			<li>Japan</li>
		</ul>
	</li>
</ul>

<br>
<H3 class="bac">Responsibilities</H3>
<p class="bac">
Research Associates will work closely with the team and some of the tasks include modeling/analysis, conducting primary research, attend internal/external client meetings. Some responsibilities are conducted regularly (daily, weekly, etc.) while others are longer-term, ad hoc projects over months. 
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications:</h2>
<br>
<H3 class="bac">Education</H3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Final year, full time MBA student graduating in 2010</li>
	<li>Bachelor/master&#39;s degree holder</li>
	<li>Outstanding academic achievement </li>
</ul>
<br>
<H3 class="bac">Experience</H3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Minimum 3 years&#39; work experience</li>
	<li>Financial services or equivalent background a plus</li>
	<li>A track record of superior performance in extracurricular and professional activities </li>
</ul>
<br>
<H3 class="bac">Skills and abilities </H3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Strong quantitative, qualitative and analytical skills </li>
	<li>Knowledge of accounting and finance</li>
	<li>Financial modeling skills and familiarity with building and maintaining information databases advantageous</li>
	<li>Ability to apply advanced oral and written communication skills to create a positive impression and professional rapport </li>
	<li>Solid communication, interpersonal, and team skills</li>
	<li>Strong marketing skills and ability, client focused</li>
	<li>Well developed judgment and business sense</li>
	<li>Responsible, efficient, detail oriented and self-motivated</li>
	<li>Ability to work independently while functioning as part of a team </li>
	<li>Demonstrated ability to multi-task and prioritize in a demanding environment to meet deadlines</li>
	<li>Appropriate language capabilities </li>
</ul>
<br>
<H3 class="bac">Personal traits</H3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>High degree of professionalism and integrity</li>
	<li>A high degree of initiative and motivation </li>
	<li>A passion for and an understanding of global financial markets and factors that impact them</li>
	<li>Quick learner and interest in taking on new responsibilities</li>
	<li>Entrepreneurial drive with commercial acumen</li>
	<li>Ability to work well with others</li>
	<li>Ability to maintain composure and confidence while juggling conflicting priorities </li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Training:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Full-time Associates are hired upon completion of their MBA.  Your career as an Associate will begin with a formal training program which takes place in New York for all Associates globally, and is considered one of the best in the industry.  Instruction is provided by Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America professionals and leading business school professors.
</p>
<p class="bac">
The training program includes:
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>A firm wide orientation program to introduce you to Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America</li>
	<li>An overview of the financial markets and essential business skills</li>
	<li>An intensive training program customized for Associates that prepares you for your placement in Research by simulating actual work assignments, covering quantitative fundamentals, and preparing you for life as an Associate</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">
After the formal training program, Associates relocate to the Asia Pacific office that hired them and begin working.  Training continues on the job and through the online learning network for continuing education as well as relevant classroom training throughout your career.
</p>

